`proxy: false` is the expected way to opt out of Axios' proxy handling, including proxy settings picked up from `HTTP_PROXY` / `HTTPS_PROXY`.

If you provide an `httpsAgent` that already handles proxying, Axios cannot reliably know that from the agent object. So if Axios also applies its own proxy config from the environment, you can effectively end up with overlapping proxy behavior, which commonly shows up as connection failures such as `socket hang up`.

Recommended pattern:

```js
