When running inside `twilio-node` (which is a Node.js environment), Axios should automatically pick the `http` adapter. If the `Authorization` header is still missing, the likely culprit is that somewhere in the chain a CORS preflight (`OPTIONS`) request is being triggered — browsers strip custom headers from preflight requests, but in pure Node.js there is no browser CORS at all.

